# 12. メイコの新作メニュー

MEIKO: Hehe. This new menu is looking good. I'm sure everyone is going to love it.
Miku: MEIKO, you here?
MEIKO: Hi, Miku. Come on in. Are you here to help out again?
MEIKO: I've already finished cleaning for the day, though. You're welcome to just relax for a while.
Miku: Is that so? In that case, could I get a coffee?
MEIKO: Of course. Oh, I just finished putting together a new menu yesterday. How would you like to be a taste tester for—
Len: Hey there, MEIKO! How's it going?
MEIKO: Oh hello, Len. As energetic as ever, I see.
Len: And Miku's here, too. You lending MEIKO a hand again?
Miku: She said I could have the day off. I just ordered a coffee.
Len: Oh, yeah? In that case, could I get a coffee too?
Miku: Len, wouldn't you rather have an orange juice?
Len: N-No! I was already thinking about ordering a coffee today!
Len: You don't always have to treat me like a kid, you know.
MEIKO: Hehe. You two really do get along, don't you?
Len: Huh? What gives you that idea? Not that I really care, though.
MEIKO: Here, Len, you can have an orange juice for now. I have a feeling this will go better with my new menu item, anyway.
Len: Oh? A new item? What is it?
MEIKO: Coffee jelly. It's not sweet like fruit or ice cream is.
Len: Oh, that's too bad.
Miku: Hehe. You're such a kid.
Len: Wh-What?! No! It's not like I'm disappointed or anything!
Miku: Oh?
Len: I love coffee jelly! I can drink coffee too, you know!
Len: I like them so much that I could even have them together!
MEIKO: Hehe. It's cute to see you acting all grown up.
Len: Hmph! I'm not acting!
Miku: All right, then. You like coffee, we get it. But MEIKO already poured you some orange juice.
Miku: Oh, now that you're here, Len, I think I'm going to step out for a bit.
Len: Huh?
Miku: MEIKO, I'll try that coffee jelly when I get back. Len, go ahead and start without me.
MEIKO: All right. Take care.
Miku: Right.
Len: Where are you going, Miku?
Miku: I've got to go get ready. I have a feeling we'll be getting some visitors soon.
Len: Visitors? You mean the ones who created this place?
Miku: Anyway, I'll be back in a little while.
Len: Huh?! Miku, wait!
Len: There she goes...
Len: No fair! I want to go with her! Miku is always leaving me behind!
MEIKO: Oh dear. If that's the case, then you should just be honest and tell her you'd like to join her.
Len: Even if I did, she'd just go off on her own. That's how she always is.
MEIKO: All right. Next time, I'll try asking her myself if she'll take you with her.
Len: It's not like I absolutely have to go with her or anything... But thanks, MEIKO.
MEIKO: Hehe. You're most welcome.
MEIKO: I know you may be a little disappointed, but I'm glad to have you here to try my coffee jelly.
Len: Really? Hehe. I'm great at taste testing! Bring it on!
MEIKO: Wonderful. I've got some whipped cream left too, so I'll give you a nice big dollop on top.
MEIKO: Here you are.
Len: Wow, it looks so good! Thanks, MEIKO!
Len: I'm a little bummed I couldn't go with Miku, but I guess taking over for her as shop assistant from time to time isn't so bad.
MEIKO: I'm happy to hear you say so. And I'll be sure to talk to her for you the next time she's here.
